{% endembed %}


<h2 id="best-practices">Best practices</h2>
<h3 id="when-to-use">When to use</h3>
<p><strong>To progressively disclose a single section of content.</strong> Details elements are useful for toggling independent sections to improve readability and navigation.</p>
<h3 id="when-not-to-use">When not to use</h3>
<p><strong>As an accordion.</strong> Details elements should not be used in groups to create makeshift accordions. They lack the proper semantics and assistive technology support, do not require that only one in a group opens at a time, and do not have the necessary UX features for accommodating multiple open sections at a time. Use the <a href="/components/accordion">accordion component</a> instead.</p>
